Definition: affected with or marked by frenzy or mania uncontrolled by reason
Example: a frenzied attack; a frenzied mob; the prosecutor's frenzied denunciation of the accused- H.W.Carter; outbursts of drunken violence and manic activity and creativity
Synonyms: manic, noun, state, mania, motive, affected, with, or, marked, by, frenzy, uncontrolled, reason, a, attack, mob, the, prosecutor, s, denunciation, of, accused, -, H, W, Carter, outbursts, drunken, violence, and, activity, creativity
Category: adj.all
